0.body: astrum is a widgeting system that depends on libcosmic it can on any wayland compositor with the layer-shell protocol. astrum is made in rust and is configured in lua i reccomend using the lua language server as that is what i will depend on for types and i reccomend getting familiar with the annotation syntax as that is what i will show in documentation
0.title: Introduction

1.body:
since this project is still a work in progress, you have to build it from source. the shell.nix contains all of the dependencies needed if you use nixos you can just run nix-shell
cargo run I also recommend having the lua language server installed in your text editor, since it contains astrum types and descriptions

---@field player string # The players name ---@class (exact) TrackMetadata

---@field album_name string # The album name of the song playing
---@field album_artists string[] # List of artists of the song
---@field length number # The length of the song in seconds

6.body: Heres what to expect out of the syntax for subscription documentation, The class that signal_data depends on will be outlied the first line like this signal_data: className and className will be defined later using lua language server annotation syntax. For subscription functions (ex. Subscriptions.hyprland:set_workspace(1)), the annoation for it will be shown\ Here are the documented services listed below. Hyprland --- Used primarily for getting workspaces from hyprland Mpris --- Used primarily for getting track data from mpris and interracting with players
